 Division II}}\n\n===Division II A===\nThe Division II A tournament was played in [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]], from 7 to 13 December 2014.<ref>[http://www.iihf.com/competition/454/statistics.html Division II A statistics]</ref>\n\n{{iht header}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|GBR}}|w=4|ow=1|ol=0|l=0|gf=22|ga=13|bc=#ccffcc}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|LTU}}|w=2|ow=1|ol=1|l=1|gf=24|ga=19}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|KOR}}|w=2|ow=1|ol=1|l=1|gf=18|ga=18}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|NED}}|w=1|ow=1|ol=0|l=3|gf=18|ga=16}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|EST}}|w=1|ow=0|ol=1|l=3|gf=12|ga=22}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|ROU}}|w=1|ow=0|ol=1|l=3|gf=18|ga=24|bc=#ffcccc}}\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"|<small>Promoted to the 2016 Division I B </small>\n| style=\"background:#ffcccc;\"|<small>Relegated to the 2016 Division II B</small>\n|}\n\n===Division II B===\nThe Division II B tournament was played in [[Jaca]], [[Spain]], from 13 to 19 December 2014.<ref>[http://www.iihf.com/competition/456/statistics.html Division II B statistics]</ref>\n\n{{iht header}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|CRO}}|w=5|ow=0|ol=0|l=0|gf=22|ga=9|bc=#ccffcc}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|ESP}}|w=4|ow=0|ol=0|l=1|gf=27|ga=10}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|AUS}}|w=2|ow=0|ol=1|l=2|gf=15|ga=15}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|BEL}}|w=1|ow=1|ol=1|l=2|gf=15|ga=17}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|SRB}}|w=1|ow=1|ol=0|l=3|gf=9|ga=19}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|ISL}}|w=0|ow=0|ol=0|l=5|gf=11|ga=29|bc=#ffcccc}}\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"|<small>Promoted to the 2016 Division II A</small>\n| style=\"background:#ffcccc;\"|<small>Relegated to the 2016 Division III</small>\n|}\n\n==Division III==\n{{Main|2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships \u2013 Division III}}\nThe Division III tournament was played in [[Dunedin]], [[New Zealand]], from 20 to 25 January 2015.<ref>[http://www.iihf.com/competition/457/statistics.html Division III statistics]</ref>\n\nOn December 27, 2014 organizers announced that the [[Bulgarian Ice Hockey Federation]] withdrew their U20 team from the tournament.<ref>[http://u20.dunedinicehockey.co.nz/about/news/bulgaria-withdraws-from-the-u-20-ice-hockey-world-championship/ Bulgaria withdraws]</ref>\n\n{{iht header}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|CHN}}|w=4|ow=0|ol=0|l=0|gf=29|ga=3|bc=#ccffcc}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|NZL}}|w=2|ow=0|ol=1|l=1|gf=13|ga=11}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|MEX}}|w=1|ow=1|ol=0|l=2|gf=8|ga=10}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|RSA}}|w=1|ow=0|ol=0|l=3|gf=4|ga=22}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|TUR}}|w=1|ow=0|ol=0|l=3|gf=7|ga=15}}\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"|<small>Promoted to the 2016 Division II B</small>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* http://www.worldjunior2015.com Official site\n* http://hockeycanada.ca/2015juniors{{Dead link|date=April 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Hockey Canada site\n\n{{IIHF World U20 Championships}}\n{{2014\u201315 in men's ice hockey}}\n\n[[Category:2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships| ]]\n[[Category:2014 in ice hockey|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:2015 in ice hockey|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:World Junior Ice Hockey Championships|2015]]\n[[Category:International ice hockey competitions hosted by Canada|2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:2014\u201315 in Canadian ice hockey|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey in Montreal|2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey in Toronto|2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:2010s in Montreal]]\n[[Category:2014 in Toronto|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:2014 in Quebec|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:2015 in Toronto|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:2015 in Quebec|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:December 2014 sports events in Canada|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:January 2015 sports events in Canada|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Montreal]]\n[[Category:International sports competitions in Toronto]]\n", "text_old": "{{redirect|2015 World Juniors|other championships|World Junior Championships (disambiguation){{!}}World Junior Championships}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Infobox International Ice Hockey Competition\n| tourney_name = IIHF World U20 Championship\n| year = 2015\n| other_titles =\n| image = 2015 WJHC logo.svg\n| size = 160\n| caption =\n| country = Canada\n| dates = December 26, 2014 \u2013 January 5, 2015\n| num_teams = 10\n| venues = [[Air Canada Centre]], [[Toronto]]<br />[[Bell Centre]], [[Montreal]]\n| cities = 2\n| winners_other = {{ihj|CAN}}\n| count = 16\n| second_other = {{ihj|RUS}}\n| third_other = {{ihj|SVK}}\n| fourth_other = {{ihj|SWE}}\n| games = 30\n| goals = 176\n| attendance = 366370\n| website = [http://www.worldjunior2015.com 2015 World Juniors]\n| scoring_leader = {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Sam Reinhart]]\n| points = 11 \n| mvp = {{flagicon|SVK}} [[Denis Godla]]\n| prevseason = [[2014 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships|2014]]\n| nextseason = [[2016 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships|2016]]\n}}\nThe '''2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships''' was the 39th edition of [[IIHF World U20 Championship|Ice Hockey World Junior Championship]], played from December 26, 2014 to January 5, 2015. It was co-hosted by [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], and [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], [[Canada]],<ref name=\"Future\">{{cite web|title=Canada to host more tourneys |url=http://www.iihf.com/channels/iihf-world-championship-oc09/home/news/news-singleview-world-championship-2009/article/canada-to-host-more-tourneys.html |date=May 9, 2010 |accessdate=January 5, 2011 |publisher=International Ice Hockey Federation |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121018123039/http://www.iihf.com/channels/iihf-world-championship-oc09/home/news/news-singleview-world-championship-2009/article/canada-to-host-more-tourneys.html |archivedate=October 18, 2012 }}</ref> and organized by [[Hockey Canada]], [[Hockey Quebec]], the [[Ontario Hockey Federation]], the [[Montreal Canadiens]], [[Maple Leafs Sports and Entertainment]] and [[Evenko]].<ref>[http://www.iihf.com/home-of-hockey/news/news-singleview/recap/8011.html?tx_ttnews%5BbackPid%5D=10&cHash=5d06d23b71 \"Heading to hockey\u2019s meccas\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130629032627/http://www.iihf.com/home-of-hockey/news/news-singleview/recap/8011.html?tx_ttnews%5BbackPid%5D=10&cHash=5d06d23b71 |date=June 29, 2013 }}, IIHF.com. June 20, 2013</ref> Games were split between [[Air Canada Centre]] in Toronto and [[Bell Centre]] in Montreal, with Montreal hosting Group A matches and two quarter finals, and Toronto hosting Group B, along with the relegation games, two quarter finals, along with the semi-finals, bronze medal, and gold medal games.<ref name=CTV-2013-06-20>[http://www.ctvnews.ca/sports/montreal-and-toronto-to-host-2015-2017-world-junior-championships-1.1333912 \"Montreal and Toronto to host 2015, 2017 world junior championships\"], Canadian Press, June 20, 2013</ref><ref name=Gazette-2013-06-20>The Gazette (Montreal), [https://montrealgazette.com/sports/World+Junior+Championship+coming+town/8555635/story.html \"World Junior Championship is coming to town\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130625043836/http://www.montrealgazette.com/sports/World+Junior+Championship+coming+town/8555635/story.html |date=June 25, 2013 }}, Brenda Branswell, June 20, 2013</ref>\n\nAfter failing to medal at the previous two editions of the tournament, [[Canada men's national junior ice hockey team|Canada]] beat [[Russia men's national junior ice hockey team|Russia]] in the final to win the gold medal, marking Canada's first medal at the World Juniors since 2012, and Canada's first gold since [[2009 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships|2009]]. [[Slovakia men's national junior ice hockey team|Slovakia]] defeated [[Sweden men's national junior ice hockey team|Sweden]] in the bronze medal game to win their second-ever medal. [[Germany men's national junior ice hockey team|Germany]] finished tenth overall and was relegated to Division IA for the 2016 tournament. Slovak goaltender [[Denis Godla]] was named the tournament's most valuable player, while [[Sam Reinhart]] of Canada was the scoring leader with 11 points.\n\n== Player eligibility ==\nA player is eligible to play in the 2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships if:<ref name=\"Main requirements for eligibility\">{{cite web |url=http://www.iihf.com/fileadmin/user_upload/PDF/The_IIHF/2012-2014_IIHF_Statutes_and_Bylaws.pdf |title=IIHF statutes and bylaws |publisher=[[International Ice Hockey Federation|IIHF]] |accessdate=2014-01-01}}</ref>\n* the player is of male gender;\n* the player was born at the earliest in 1995, and at the latest, in 2000;\n* the player is a citizen in the country he represents;\n* the player is under the jurisdiction of a national association that is a member of the [[International Ice Hockey Federation|IIHF]].\n\nIf a player who has never played in IIHF-organized competition wishes to switch national eligibility, he must have played in competitions for two consecutive years in the new country without playing in another country, as well as show his move to the new country's national association with an international transfer card. In case the player has previously played in IIHF-organized competition but wishes to switch national eligibility, he must have played in competitions for four consecutive years in the new country without playing in another country, he must show his move to the new country's national association with an international transfer card, as well as be a citizen of the new country. A player may only switch national eligibility once.<ref name=\"Requirements for switching national eligibility\">{{cite web |url=http://www.iihf.com/home-of-hockey/championships/iihf-eligibility.html |title=IIHF Eligibility |publisher=[[International Ice Hockey Federation|IIHF]] |accessdate=2014-01-01}}</ref>\n\n==Top Division==\n===Venues===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! [[Toronto]]\n!rowspan=5 colspan=2|{{Location map+ |Canada |width=350 |float=center |caption= |places=\n{{Location map~ |Canada |lat=45.508889 |long=-73.561667 |label=[[Montreal]]|position=right}}\n{{Location map~ |Canada |lat=43.741667 |long=-79.373333 |label=[[Toronto]]|position=left}}\n}}\n! [[Montreal]]\n|-\n! [[Air Canada Centre]]<br/>Capacity: 18,819\n! [[Bell Centre]]<br />Capacity: 21,287\n|-\n| [[File:Air Canada Centre and CN Tower from Bay St.jpg|150px]]\n| [[File:CentreBell.jpg|150px]]\n|}\n\n===Officials===\nThe [[IIHF]] selected 12 referees and 10 linesmen to officiate during the tournament:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldjunior2015.com/en/news/officials-known/|title=Officials Known|publisher=IIHF.com|accessdate=5 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n'''Referees'''\n* {{flagicon|SVK}} Vladim\u00edr Balu\u0161ka\n* {{flagicon|GER}} Lars Bruggemann\n* {{flagicon|RUS}} Roman Gofman\n* {{flagicon|CZE}} Antonin Je\u0159\u00e1bek\n* {{flagicon|FIN}} Mikko Kaukokari\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Geoffrey Miller\n* {{flagicon|SWE}} Linus \u00d6hlund\n* {{flagicon|RUS}} Konstantin Olenin\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Steve Patafie\n* {{flagicon|CAN}} Pascal St-Jaques\n* {{flagicon|SWE}} Marcus Vinnerborg\n* {{flagicon|SUI}} Tobias Wehrli\n{{col-3}}\n'''Linesmen'''\n* {{flagicon|CAN}} Jordan Browne\n* {{flagicon|FRA}} Pierre Dehaen\n* {{flagicon|RUS}} Gleb Lazarev\n* {{flagicon|CZE}} Miroslav Lhotsk\u00fd\n* {{flagicon|SWE}} Andreas Malmqvist\n* {{flagicon|CAN}} Bevan Mills\n* {{flagicon|FIN}} Jani Pesonen\n* {{flagicon|GER}} Nikolaj Ponomarjow\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Judson Ritter\n* {{flagicon|SUI}} Simon Wust\n{{col-3}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Format===\nThe four best ranked teams from each group of the preliminary round advance to the quarterfinals, while the last placed teams from each group played a relegation round in a [[Playoff format#Best-of-three playoff|best of three]] format to determine the relegated team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iihf.com/home-of-hockey/news/news-singleview/?tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=7006&cHash=3fc42c5c221ed1fe6cdb1b0461a9ce05|title=New format for U18, U20 Worlds|date=2012-05-29|work=[[IIHF]].com|accessdate=2011-05-29}}</ref>\n\n===Rosters===\n{{Main|2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships rosters}}\n\n=== Preliminary round ===\n<small>''All times are local. ([[Eastern Time Zone|Eastern Standard Time]] \u2013 [[UTC-5]])''</small>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ccffcc;width:22px\" |\n|Team qualified to Quarterfinals\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ffcccc;\" |\n|Team will play in Relegation round\n|}\n\n====Group A====\n{{iht header}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|CAN}}|w=4|ow=0|ol=0|l=0|gf=21|ga=4|bc=#ccffcc}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|USA}}|w=2|ow=1|ol=0|l=1|gf=14|ga=6|bc=#ccffcc}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|SVK}}|w=2|ow=0|ol=0|l=2|gf=7|ga=14|bc=#ccffcc}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|FIN}}|w=1|ow=0|ol=1|l=2|gf=5|ga=8|bc=#ccffcc}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|GER}}|w=0|ow=0|ol=0|l=4|gf=2|ga=17|bc=#ffcccc}}\n|}\n\n{{IceHockeybox\n| date = December 26, 2014\n| time = 15:00\n| team1 = {{ihj-rt|FIN}}\n| score = 1\u20132 <small> [[Shootout (ice hockey)|GWS]] </small>\n| team2 = '''{{ihj|USA}}'''\n| progression = 1\u20130<br>1\u20131\n| periods = (1\u20131, 0\u20130, 0\u20130)<br>([[sudden death overtime|OT]] 0\u20130)<br>([[Shootout (ice hockey)|SO]]: 1\u20132)\n| goalie1 = [[Ville Husso]]\n| goalie2 = [[Thatcher Demko]]\n| goals1 = [[Mikko Rantanen|M. Rantanen]] \u2013 01:22\n| soshots1 = [[Artturi Lehkonen|A. Lehkonen]] {{SOgoal}}<br>[[Juuso Ikonen|J. Ikonen]] {{SOmiss}}<br>[[Kasperi Kapanen|K. Kapanen]] {{SOmiss}}\n| goals2 = <br>13:54 \u2013 [[Alex Tuch|A. Tuch]] ([[Jack Eichel|J. Eichel]], [[Tony DeAngelo|A. DeAngelo]]) (PP)\n| soshots2 = {{SOgoal}} J. Eichel<br>{{SOmiss}} [[Sonny Milano|S. Milano]]<br>{{SOgoal}} [[Chase de Leo|C. de Leo]]\n| attendanc