ated to the 2016 Division I A</small>\n|}\n{{col-3}}\n{{winners|ihj|2015 IIHF Junior World Champions|CAN|16th}}\n{{col-3}}\n{{col-end}}\nNote that due to the lack of playoff games for determining the spots 5\u20138, these spots were determined by the preliminary round records for each team.\n\n==Division I==\n{{Main|2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships \u2013 Division I}}\n\n===Division I A===\nThe Division I A tournament was played in [[Asiago]], [[Italy]], from 14 to 20 December 2014.<ref>[http://www.iihf.com/competition/451/statistics.html Division I A statistics]</ref>\n\n{{iht header}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|BLR}}|w=4|ow=1|ol=0|l=0|gf=22|ga=9|bc=#ccffcc}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|NOR}}|w=2|ow=2|ol=0|l=1|gf=16|ga=11}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|LAT}}|w=2|ow=0|ol=1|l=2|gf=15|ga=11}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|ITA}}|w=1|ow=1|ol=0|l=3|gf=16|ga=22}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|AUT}}|w=1|ow=0|ol=2|l=2|gf=21|ga=27}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|SLO}}|w=1|ow=0|ol=1|l=3|gf=17|ga=27|bc=#ffcccc}}\n|}\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"|<small>Promoted to the 2016 Top Division</small>\n|style=\"background:#ffcccc;\"|<small>Relegated to the 2016 Division I B</small>\n|}\n\n===Division I B===\nThe Division I B tournament was played in [[Duna\u00fajv\u00e1ros]], [[Hungary]], from 14 to 20 December 2014.<ref>[http://www.iihf.com/competition/453/statistics.html Division I B statistics]</ref>\n\n{{iht header}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|KAZ}}|w=5|ow=0|ol=0|l=0|gf=23|ga=9|bc=#ccffcc}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|UKR}}|w=2|ow=1|ol=0|l=2|gf=10|ga=11}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|POL}}|w=2|ow=0|ol=1|l=2|gf=13|ga=15}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|FRA}}|w=2|ow=0|ol=1|l=2|gf=11|ga=13}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|JPN}}|w=1|ow=1|ol=0|l=3|gf=15|ga=17}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|HUN}}|w=0|ow=1|ol=1|l=3|gf=9|ga=16|bc=#ffcccc}}\n|}\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"|<small>Promoted to the 2016 Division I A</small>\n|style=\"background:#ffcccc;\"|<small>Relegated to the 2016 Division II A</small>\n|}\n\n==Division II==\n{{Main|2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships \u2013 Division II}}\n\n===Division II A===\nThe Division II A tournament was played in [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]], from 7 to 13 December 2014.<ref>[http://www.iihf.com/competition/454/statistics.html Division II A statistics]</ref>\n\n{{iht header}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|GBR}}|w=4|ow=1|ol=0|l=0|gf=22|ga=13|bc=#ccffcc}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|LTU}}|w=2|ow=1|ol=1|l=1|gf=24|ga=19}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|KOR}}|w=2|ow=1|ol=1|l=1|gf=18|ga=18}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|NED}}|w=1|ow=1|ol=0|l=3|gf=18|ga=16}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|EST}}|w=1|ow=0|ol=1|l=3|gf=12|ga=22}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|ROU}}|w=1|ow=0|ol=1|l=3|gf=18|ga=24|bc=#ffcccc}}\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"|<small>Promoted to the 2016 Division I B </small>\n| style=\"background:#ffcccc;\"|<small>Relegated to the 2016 Division II B</small>\n|}\n\n===Division II B===\nThe Division II B tournament was played in [[Jaca]], [[Spain]], from 13 to 19 December 2014.<ref>[http://www.iihf.com/competition/456/statistics.html Division II B statistics]</ref>\n\n{{iht header}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|CRO}}|w=5|ow=0|ol=0|l=0|gf=22|ga=9|bc=#ccffcc}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|ESP}}|w=4|ow=0|ol=0|l=1|gf=27|ga=10}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|AUS}}|w=2|ow=0|ol=1|l=2|gf=15|ga=15}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|BEL}}|w=1|ow=1|ol=1|l=2|gf=15|ga=17}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|SRB}}|w=1|ow=1|ol=0|l=3|gf=9|ga=19}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|ISL}}|w=0|ow=0|ol=0|l=5|gf=11|ga=29|bc=#ffcccc}}\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"|<small>Promoted to the 2016 Division II A</small>\n| style=\"background:#ffcccc;\"|<small>Relegated to the 2016 Division III</small>\n|}\n\n==Division III==\n{{Main|2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships \u2013 Division III}}\nThe Division III tournament was played in [[Dunedin]], [[New Zealand]], from 20 to 25 January 2015.<ref>[http://www.iihf.com/competition/457/statistics.html Division III statistics]</ref>\n\nOn December 27, 2014 organizers announced that the [[Bulgarian Ice Hockey Federation]] withdrew their U20 team from the tournament.<ref>[http://u20.dunedinicehockey.co.nz/about/news/bulgaria-withdraws-from-the-u-20-ice-hockey-world-championship/ Bulgaria withdraws]</ref>\n\n{{iht header}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|CHN}}|w=4|ow=0|ol=0|l=0|gf=29|ga=3|bc=#ccffcc}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|NZL}}|w=2|ow=0|ol=1|l=1|gf=13|ga=11}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|MEX}}|w=1|ow=1|ol=0|l=2|gf=8|ga=10}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|RSA}}|w=1|ow=0|ol=0|l=3|gf=4|ga=22}}\n{{iht team|t={{ihj|TUR}}|w=1|ow=0|ol=0|l=3|gf=7|ga=15}}\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"|<small>Promoted to the 2016 Division II B</small>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* http://www.worldjunior2015.com Official site\n* http://hockeycanada.ca/2015juniors{{Dead link|date=April 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Hockey Canada site\n\n{{IIHF World U20 Championships}}\n{{2014\u201315 in men's ice hockey}}\n\n[[Category:2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships| ]]\n[[Category:2014 in ice hockey|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:2015 in ice hockey|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:World Junior Ice Hockey Championships|2015]]\n[[Category:International ice hockey competitions hosted by Canada|2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:2014\u201315 in Canadian ice hockey|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey in Montreal|2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey in Toronto|2015 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:2014 in Ontario|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:2014 in Quebec|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:2015 in Ontario|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:2015 in Quebec|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:December 2014 sports events in Canada|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:January 2015 sports events in Canada|World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Montreal]]\n[[Category:International sports competitions in Toronto]]\n[[Category:2010s in Montreal]]\n[[Category:2014 in Toronto]]\n[[Category:2015 in Toronto]]\n", "name_user": "KingSkyLord", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2015_World_Junior_Ice_Hockey_Championships"}
{"title_page": "Ernest Wichner", "text_new": "{{Expand German|Ernest Wichner|date=January 2013}}\n'''Ernest Wichner''' (born in [[Z\u0103brani]], 17 April 1952) is a German writer, editor, and literary translator.\n\n==Translations==\n* [[Norman Manea]]: ''Der Trenchcoat.'' Erz\u00e4hlung. Steidl Verlag, G\u00f6ttingen 1990\n* [[Max Blecher]]: ''Aus der unmittelbaren Unwirklichkeit''. Prosa, \u00fcbersetzt und mit einem Nachwort versehen von Ernest Wichner, Edition Plasma, Berlin 1990 (Neuausgabe mit Nachwort von [[Herta M\u00fcller]], Bibliothek Suhrkamp, Frankfurt a.M. 2003)\n* [[Carmen-Francesca Banciu]]: ''Fenster in Flammen.'' Erz\u00e4hlungen, \u00fcbersetzt von Ernest Wichner und Rolf Bossert, Rotbuch Verlag, Berlin 1992\n* \u0218tefan B\u0103nulescu: ''Ein Schneesturm aus anderer Zeit.'' Erz\u00e4hlungen, \u00fcbersetzt von Ernest Wichner und Oskar Pastior, Nachwort von Ernest Wichner, Suhrkamp Verlag, Frankfurt a.M. 1994\n* [[Dumitru \u021aepeneag]]: ''Hotel Europa.'' Roman, Alexander Fest Verlag, Berlin 1998 (Taschenbuch Suhrkamp, Verlag Frankfurt a.M. 2000)\n* Daniel B\u0103nulescu: ''Schrumpeln wirst du wirst eine exotische Frucht sein''. Gedichte (rum./dt.), aus dem Rum\u00e4nischen und mit einem Nachwort von Ernest Wichner, edition per procura, Wien/Lana 2003\n* [[Nora Iuga]]: ''Der Autobus mit den Buckligen.'' Gedichte, aus dem Rum\u00e4nischen von Ernest Wichner, Edition Solitude, Stuttgart 2003\n* M. Blecher: ''Vernarbte Herzen''. Roman, \u00fcbersetzt und mit einem Nachwort von Ernest Wichner, Bibliothek Suhrkamp, Frankfurt a.M., 2006\n* Cristian Popescu: ''Familie Popescu'', Prosa (rum./dt.), aus dem Rum\u00e4nischen von Ernest Wichner, edition per procura, Wien/Lana 2006\n* Nora Iuga: ''Gef\u00e4hrliche Launen.'' Ausgew\u00e4hlte Gedichte, aus dem Rum\u00e4nischen von Ernest Wichner, mit einem Nachwort von Mircea C\u01cert\u01cerescu, Verlag Klett-Cotta, Stuttgart 2007\n* M. Blecher: ''Beleuchtete H\u00f6hle.'' Sanatoriumstagebuch, \u00fcbersetzt und mit einem Nachwort von Ernest Wichner, Bibliothek Suhrkamp, Frankfurt a.M. 2008\n* Ion Mure\u0219an: ''Acces interzis!/Zugang verboten!'' Gedichte (rum./dt.), ausgew\u00e4hlt, mit einem Nachwort und \u00fcbersetzt von Ernest Wichner, b\u00fcroabrasch, Wien 2008\n* Mircea C\u0103rt\u0103rescu: ''Warum wir die Frauen lieben.'' Geschichten, aus dem Rum\u00e4nischen von Ernest Wichner, Suhrkamp, Frankfurt a.M. 2008\n* Daniel B\u0103nulescu: ''Was sch\u00f6n ist und dem Daniel gef\u00e4llt.'' Gedichte, \u00fcbersetzt und mit einem Nachwort versehen von Ernest Wichner; merz&solitude, Stuttgart 2009\n* Christopher Middleton: ''Im geheimen Haus''. Gedichte englisch-deutsch, \u00fcbersetzt von Ernest Wichner, Verlag Das Wunderhorn, Heidelberg 2009\n* [[Mircea C\u0103rt\u0103rescu]]: ''Travestie'', Suhrkamp Verlag, Berlin 2010 {{ISBN|978-3-518-42179-6}}\n\n== Awards==\n* 1987 F\u00f6rderpreis zum [[Marburger Literaturpreis]]\n* 1990 Stipendium [[K\u00fcnstlerhaus Edenkoben]]\n* 1991 F\u00f6rderpreis zum [[Andreas-Gryphius-Preis]]\n* 1997 Lyrik-Stipendium Niedersachsen\n* 2005 [[Preis der Stadt M\u00fcnster f\u00fcr Europ\u00e4ische Poesie]] (with Daniel Banulescu)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{DNB-Portal|123468507}}\n* [http://www.literaturhaeuser.net/netzwerk/berlin_pers.htm Ernest Wichner] bei literaturhaeuser.net\n*[http://halbjahresschrift.blogspot.de/2012/04/40-jahre-aktionsgruppe-banat.html 40 Jahre Aktionsgruppe Banat, in: ''Halbjahresschrift - hjs-online'', 2. April 2012]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wichner, Ernest}}\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:People from Arad County]]\n[[Category:German editors]]\n[[Category:German translators]]\n[[Category:Translators from Romanian]]\n[[Category:Translators to German]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:German male non-fiction writers]]\n\n\n{{Germany-translator-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Expand German|Ernest Wichner|date=January 2013}}\n'''Ernest Wichner''' (born in [[Z\